  "Mercury has hydrogen bonds while water does not": "",
  "Mercury is denser than water, so gravity pulls it into spheres": "",
  "Mercury atoms have strong metallic bonding (cohesion) but very weak adhesion to most surfaces. Since cohesion dominates over adhesion, mercury minimizes its surface area by forming spherical droplets.": "",
  "A mountaineer boils water at a high-altitude camp and notices it boils at only 85°C instead of 100°C. The food takes longer to cook. What intermolecular force concept explains why water boils at a lower temperature at high altitude?": "",
