  "UV radiation at high altitude breaks hydrogen bonds, which is a common assumption in the field": "",
  "The lower atmospheric pressure at high altitude means less external pressure holding water molecules in the liquid phase, so they escape as vapor at a lower temperature": "",
  "Boiling occurs when vapor pressure equals atmospheric pressure. At high altitude, atmospheric pressure is lower, so water's vapor pressure reaches it at a lower temperature. The IMFs themselves don't change.": "",
  "A pharmaceutical company develops a transdermal drug patch that delivers medication through the skin. The drug must be able to pass through the nonpolar lipid bilayer of skin cells. Which molecular property would make a drug molecule more effective for transdermal delivery?": "",
