  "Effective transdermal drugs need a balance: enough nonpolar character (LDF interactions) to cross the lipid bilayer of skin, but enough polar character to dissolve in aqueous blood once absorbed. This is the concept of lipophilicity.": "",
  "A materials engineer is comparing two substances for use as a lubricant: a long-chain hydrocarbon (C₃₀H₆₂) and a short-chain hydrocarbon (C₈H₁₈). Both are nonpolar. Why would the long-chain hydrocarbon be a better lubricant?": "",
